In NY, there are no actual tollbooths on the Thruway, the main toll highway in the state.  If you don't have EZ Pass or a compatible device, you are billed by mail at a higher rate.  All business is taken care of by overhead gantries, and the lanes do not have any obstacles or barriers.  Traffic flows at normal speed.

I can't remember if all the NYC bridge and tunnel tollbooths are gone, but if they aren't yet, they're on the way out.

